This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel objective function for GANs. It also involves optimization and training of GANs, which are common topics in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed method is evaluated on standard image synthesis benchmarks of computer vision. 

Additionally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular topic in AI research. 

The sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as GANs are a type of neural network and the paper involves optimization of the network. 

Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) as the paper deals with image synthesis, which is a common topic in graphics research.
